From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:01:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] BCM SEC16: honest shared-constant flag + grounded findings
 doc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Proven on the SCAT married set that the marry algebra is correct
(RFH[0x050E]=reverse16(BCM split); PCM[0x3C8]=reverse(BCM)[0:6]; marker
FFFFFFAA). The bug was never the math — it's that on un-programmed/donor
BCMs the resolver falls back to the 00..313E..0A block, which is
byte-identical across 3 unrelated cars (527958/592745/539430) and only
appears when split records are blank. Its status as a real family secret
is unresolved (codebase claims SINCRO; no married constant-set to prove it).

So instead of guessing either way: resolveBcmSec16 now flags
bcmSec16.sharedConstant (bytes unchanged -> all 704 BCM tests preserved),
and crossValidate warns so marry/key flows never treat it as a confident
per-car secret. Evidence + the one unresolved question documented in
BCM_SECRET_FINDINGS.md. Full suite: 5843 passed, 7 pre-existing failures,
zero new.
